The Debating Society of NSUT
30 March ·

Only a week after successfully pulling off Colloquium 2019 - the very own literary and debating festival of NSUT, the sophomore and freshman year members of our society have given us an other reason to celebrate.

We extend our heartiest congratulations to Rishabh Rathi, Mehul Singh and Rudresh Pratap Singh for breaking as a debating team in QED'19, Parliamentary Debating tournament held at BITS Pilani, reaching the Semi Finals.

Aditya Bhatnagar, a freshman year member of our society displayed an equally exceptional performance, breaking as an adjudicator in the very same tournament.

We wish them all the best for all the future tournaments and hope they keep performing exceptionally well.

The Debating Society of NSUT
11 hrs ·

The Debating Society of NSUT is extremely proud to announce its achievements at SYMUNC'19, Symbiosis Centre For Management Studies, Noida, bagging several awards at the conference.

Our members bagged the following awards:

1. Saumya Singh: Honourable Mention...
2. Mitansh Khurana: Honourable Mention
3. T. Sai Ganesh: Verbal Mention
4. Akshit Pareek: Special Mention
5. Vaibhav Sharma: Special Mention
6. Dhruv Bhardwaj: Special Mention
7. Ayush Kumar: Special Mention

Congratulations to all the freshers and sophomores!

The Debating Society of NSUT
12 October at 18:50 ·

The Debating Society of NSUT in collaboration with Jamboree Education presents an exclusive counselling session on MS and PhD/MBA in India and abroad.

Covering all related topics such as admission criteria for Universities abroad, masters programs available, scholarships and more, this session will clear all your doubts. It will guide you through strategies to score in GMAT and GRE and even help improve your profile. Experts from Jamboree with more than 26 years of experience... will help provide a better and more informed outlook towards further education in India and abroad.

None other than Mr Soumyo Gupta, CEO of Jamboree, will be conducting the session. His expertise and experience in the field of education will help you realize the right career path for you.

Opportunities are at your doorstep, so look no further and join us on Wednesday, 16th October in the Main Auditorium at 4:00 PM!
